    <h2 class="drizzle-b-h2">Welcome</h2>
    <p>This guide is intended for applications that are not using a JS front-end framework, such as Angular or React.
    Follow the instructions below to incorporate Spark into your project.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="drizzle-o-ContentGrouping">
    <h2 class="drizzle-b-h2 sprk-u-mbm">Quick Start (Spark-Core only)</h2>
    <div class="drizzle-o-ContentGrouping drizzle-u-pll">
      <p>These instructions are for quickly getting Spark set up. Details around each step are omitted and they
      assume that you won't be using any Spark Extras packages. See below for more detailed instructions.</p>

      <ol>
        <li class="sprk-u-mbm">
          <p class="sprk-u-mbn"><strong>Install Spark Core</strong></p>
          <div class="drizzle-c-Command">
            <code class="drizzle-CodeHighlight">npm install --save-dev @sparkdesignsystem/spark-core</code>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="sprk-u-mbm">
          <p class="sprk-u-mbn"><strong>Import Spark Core SCSS</strong></p>
          <div class="drizzle-c-Command">
            <code class="drizzle-CodeHighlight">@import "node_modules/@sparkdesignsystem/spark-core/spark-core"</code>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="sprk-u-mbm">
          <p class="sprk-u-mbn"><strong>Import Spark Core Prerender JS</strong></p>
          <p>You'll need to create another file that will import sparkCorePrerender and call it with your
            configuration options. The output of building this file will need to be loaded in the application's
            &lt;head&gt; element.</p>
          <div class="sprk-b-TypeBodyTwo drizzle-c-Preview">
            <div class="drizzle-c-Preview__code">
