  <div class="drizzle-o-ContentGrouping">
    <h3 class="drizzle-b-h3">Styles</h3>
    <p>Spark assumes your project is using
      <a class="drizzle-b-Link" href="https://sass-lang.com/">Sass</a> for styling. You'll need to incorporate the
    spark-core scss file into your sass build, before any of your application's scss is imported.</p>
    <div class="drizzle-c-Command sprk-u-mbm">
      <code class="drizzle-CodeHighlight">
        @import "node_modules/@sparkdesignsystem/spark-core/spark-core</code>
    </div>
    <p>Spark's style values are mostly overridable. See the variable section on each component's documentation page for
      available options.</p>
    <p>Any component variables that you want to override need to be placed <strong>before</strong>
      the spark-core import statement.</p>
  </div>

